# Recovery Point verification log example
#
# This file is a placeholder that demonstrates the generated output expected
# after a Recovery Point verification process.
#
# The verification automation creates the real file as:
#
#   verification.log
#
# Expected log entries may include:
#
# - Recovery Point ID
# - Verification start and completion timestamps
# - Required-file checks
# - Directory-structure checks
# - Checksum validation results
# - Archive integrity results
# - Warnings or failures
# - Final verification status
#
# Example output:
#
# 2026-07-17 22:30:00 [INFO] Verification started for RP-20260717-001
# 2026-07-17 22:30:00 [PASS] Required file found: RP_MANIFEST.md
# 2026-07-17 22:30:00 [PASS] Required file found: SYSTEM_RECOVERY_MANUAL.md
# 2026-07-17 22:30:01 [PASS] SHA-256 checksum validation completed
# 2026-07-17 22:30:01 [INFO] Verification status: COMPLETE
#
# This example is documentation only and is not evidence that a Recovery Point
# has been verified.
